<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Application limits ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
It must be taken into account that the obtained results represented in the graphs must be inside the application limits of the method.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The application limits of the Blount and Fox correction method are:
</div>

<math> F_\Delta \geq 1.0 </math>

<math> \frac{LCG}{L_P} \leq 0.46 </math>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Where:
* <math> F_\Delta </math> is the volumetric Froude number, defined by the following expression:<br><math> F_\Delta = \frac{V}{\sqrt{g\nabla^{\frac{1}{3}}}} </math>
* <math> LCG </math> is the longitudinal center of gravity of the vessel.
* <math> L_P </math> is the projected keel length of the vessel.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
These limits extend the application of the Savitsky method to low-speed conditions.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Usage ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
This tool does not have a strict dependency on a '''Ship instance'''(see [[Ship_CreateShip|Ship CreateShip]]), which means that it is possible to use it introducing the necessary ship data values in the dialogue.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Using ship geometry ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
In order to execute the method, select a '''Ship instance''' and invoke {{MenuCommand|Resistance → [[Image:Ship_ResistanceBlountFox.svg|16px]] Resistance Blount and Fox prediction}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The ship data will be obtain from the ship and the user only needs to enter the boundary conditions.
Data obtained from the vessel can be edited.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Using ship data ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
In order to introduced the ship data manually execute the method, invoke {{MenuCommand|Resistance → [[Image:Ship_ResistanceBlountFox.svg|16px]] Resistance Blount and Fox prediction}} and fill the dialogue fields.
</div>

